The paper deals with the complexity of counting problems, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The concept of Holant problems is related to constraint satisfaction problems, which are studied in cs.GT (computational game theory). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between windability and expressibility, which is a topic in information theory and communication theory, and thus falls under cs.IT (information theory).
